                           <p>A <material>white marble</material>
                              <objectType>altar-stele</objectType> with moulding above and below on three sides (<dimensions><height unit="metre">0.80</height> <width unit="metre">0.37</width> <depth unit="metre">0.37</depth></dimensions>). 
                              The relief, which is largely lost, is of a <rs type="decoration">bestiarius</rs> standing, facing to his right; one arm can be made out, held behind his back. He confronts a creature, which is jumping up at him. 
                              Above the man's head is a triangular area in relief, from which all features have been lost. For a full description see Kontokosta (2008).</p>
